{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.18",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 18 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:1",
      "text": "I love thee, O Lord, my strength.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:2",
      "text": "The Lord is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer, my God, my rock, in whom I take refuge, my shield, and the horn of my salvation, my stronghold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:3",
      "text": "I call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised, and I am saved from my enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:4",
      "text": "The cords of death encompassed me, the torrents of perdition assailed me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:5",
      "text": "the cords of Sheol entangled me, the snares of death confronted me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:6",
      "text": "In my distress I called upon the Lord; to my God I cried for help. From his temple he heard my voice, and my cry to him reached his ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:7",
      "text": "Then the earth reeled and rocked; the foundations also of the mountains trembled and quaked, because he was angry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:8",
      "text": "Smoke went up from his nostrils, and devouring fire from his mouth; glowing coals flamed forth from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:9",
      "text": "He bowed the heavens, and came down; thick darkness was under his feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:10",
      "text": "He rode on a cherub, and flew; he came swiftly upon the wings of the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:11",
      "text": "He made darkness his covering around him, his canopy thick clouds dark with water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:12",
      "text": "Out of the brightness before him there broke through his clouds hailstones and coals of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:13",
      "text": "The Lord also thundered in the heavens, and the Most High uttered his voice, hailstones and coals of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:14",
      "text": "And he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; he flashed forth lightnings, and routed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:15",
      "text": "Then the channels of the sea were seen, and the foundations of the world were laid bare, at thy rebuke, O Lord, at the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:16",
      "text": "He reached from on high, he took me, he drew me out of many waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:17",
      "text": "He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from those who hated me; for they were too mighty for me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:18",
      "text": "They came upon me in the day of my calamity; but the Lord was my stay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:19",
      "text": "He brought me forth into a broad place; he delivered me, because he delighted in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:20",
      "text": "The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands he recompensed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:21",
      "text": "For I have kept the ways of the Lord, and have not wickedly departed from my God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:22",
      "text": "For all his ordinances were before me, and his statutes I did not put away from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:23",
      "text": "I was blameless before him, and I kept myself from guilt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:24",
      "text": "Therefore the Lord has recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:25",
      "text": "With the loyal thou dost show thyself loyal; with the blameless man thou dost show thyself blameless;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:26",
      "text": "with the pure thou dost show thyself pure; and with the crooked thou dost show thyself perverse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:27",
      "text": "For thou dost deliver a humble people; but the haughty eyes thou dost bring down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:28",
      "text": "Yea, thou dost light my lamp; the Lord my God lightens my darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:29",
      "text": "Yea, by thee I can crush a troop; and by my God I can leap over a wall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:30",
      "text": "This God—his way is perfect; the promise of the Lord proves true; he is a shield for all those who take refuge in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:31",
      "text": "For who is God, but the Lord? And who is a rock, except our God?—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:32",
      "text": "the God who girded me with strength, and made my way safe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:33",
      "text": "He made my feet like hinds' feet, and set me secure on the heights.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:34",
      "text": "He trains my hands for war, so that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:35",
      "text": "Thou hast given me the shield of thy salvation, and thy right hand supported me, and thy help made me great.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:36",
      "text": "Thou didst give a wide place for my steps under me, and my feet did not slip.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:37",
      "text": "I pursued my enemies and overtook them; and did not turn back till they were consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:38",
      "text": "I thrust them through, so that they were not able to rise; they fell under my feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:39",
      "text": "For thou didst gird me with strength for the battle; thou didst make my assailants sink under me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:40",
      "text": "Thou didst make my enemies turn their backs to me, and those who hated me I destroyed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:41",
      "text": "They cried for help, but there was none to save, they cried to the Lord, but he did not answer them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:42",
      "text": "I beat them fine as dust before the wind; I cast them out like the mire of the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:43",
      "text": "Thou didst deliver me from strife with the peoples; thou didst make me the head of the nations; people whom I had not known served me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:44",
      "text": "As soon as they heard of me they obeyed me; foreigners came cringing to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:45",
      "text": "Foreigners lost heart, and came trembling out of their fastnesses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:46",
      "text": "The Lord lives; and blessed be my rock, and exalted be the God of my salvation,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:47",
      "text": "the God who gave me vengeance and subdued peoples under me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:48",
      "text": "who delivered me from my enemies; yea, thou didst exalt me above my adversaries; thou didst deliver me from men of violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:49",
      "text": "For this I will extol thee, O Lord, among the nations, and sing praises to thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.18.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:50",
      "text": "Great triumphs he gives to his king, and shows steadfast love to his anointed, to David and his descendants for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
